## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of up-to-date data and the inherent biases in publicly available sources. Additionally, the complexity of nuclear hazards and their comparison to other risks may not be fully captured in the available literature. Further research, including expert interviews and access to proprietary databases, could provide a more comprehensive understanding.